OL,3,CBirmingham pub bombings 50 years on:
OL,4,CFamilies demand public inquiry
OL,6,FNow Julie Hambleton, who founded the
OL,7,F'Justice 4 the 21' group, believes
OL,8,Fonly a statutory public inquiry will
OL,9,Fforce the disclosure of secret
OL,10,Fdocuments.
OL,12,F"Who did it? How long have you known?
OL,13,FWhy didn't you act? Did you have any
OL,14,Fpre-warnings?" are among the
OL,15,F"cacophony" of questions Julie has for
OL,16,Fthe police and British state.
OL,18,F"We will not go away," she says,
OL,19,F"until we have that for our loved ones
OL,20,Fand the survivors."
